---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const canonical = new URL('/demo/passkey/', Astro.site).toString();
---

<BaseLayout
	title="passkey demo — millsymills.com"
	description="webauthn passkey register + authenticate demo with a mock backend. sandbox; no real account."
	canonical={canonical}
	noindex
>
	<div class="passkey">
		<header class="passkey__head">
			<p class="passkey__eyebrow" aria-hidden="true">/ DEMO / PASSKEY</p>
			<h1 class="passkey__title">passkey demo</h1>
			<p class="passkey__lede">
				exercise <code>navigator.credentials.create()</code> and
				<code>navigator.credentials.get()</code> against a mock backend.
				the real lambda lands in the #140 logic slice.
			</p>
		</header>

		<aside class="passkey__notice" role="note" aria-label="sandbox notice">
			<strong>sandbox.</strong> no real account is created. credentials live in
			<code>localStorage</code> only and can be cleared at any time. authenticator
			challenges are generated client-side; nothing is sent to a server in this
			demo. credentials expire automatically when you clear browser storage for
			this origin.
		</aside>

		<section class="passkey__demo" data-passkey-demo>
			<div class="passkey__stored" data-stored-view data-state="empty">
				no credential registered yet.
			</div>

			<div class="passkey__row">
				<h2 class="passkey__h2">register</h2>
				<p class="passkey__copy">
					create a new credential bound to this origin. supply a synthetic
					display name — no email, no PII.
				</p>
				<label class="passkey__field">
					<span>display name</span>
					<input
						type="text"
						maxlength="40"
						placeholder="demo user"
						autocomplete="off"
						spellcheck="false"
						data-passkey-name
					/>
				</label>
				<div class="passkey__actions">
					<button type="button" class="passkey__btn" data-action="register">
						register credential
					</button>
				</div>
				<p class="passkey__status" data-status="register" data-state="idle"
					role="status" aria-live="polite"></p>
			</div>

			<div class="passkey__row">
				<h2 class="passkey__h2">authenticate</h2>
				<p class="passkey__copy">
					assert with the credential you just registered. the mock backend
					checks that the returned credential id matches the stored one.
				</p>
				<div class="passkey__actions">
					<button type="button" class="passkey__btn" data-action="authenticate">
						authenticate
					</button>
					<button type="button" class="passkey__btn passkey__btn--ghost"
						data-action="clear">
						clear credential
					</button>
				</div>
				<p class="passkey__status" data-status="authenticate" data-state="idle"
					role="status" aria-live="polite"></p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="passkey__writeup">
			<h2 class="passkey__h2">what's going on under the hood</h2>

			<h3 class="passkey__h3">origin binding (rpID)</h3>
			<p>
				the relying party id (<code>rpID</code>) is set to the page's hostname.
				webauthn refuses to use a credential against any origin that doesn't
				match the rpID, so a credential registered at <code>millsymills.com</code>
				cannot be replayed against a phishing site at <code>m1llsymills.com</code>
				— the browser enforces the binding before the credential is ever
				retrieved. this is the load-bearing property that makes passkeys
				phishing-resistant. server-side rpID validation is a backstop, not
				the primary control.
			</p>

			<h3 class="passkey__h3">attestation: <code>none</code></h3>
			<p>
				the spec defines four attestation conveyance preferences:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li><code>none</code> — no attestation statement; the rp accepts the
					credential without knowing the authenticator model.</li>
				<li><code>indirect</code> — the rp accepts anonymized attestation;
					some browsers issue an enterprise-friendly batch attestation.</li>
				<li><code>direct</code> — the rp wants the raw attestation statement,
					including the manufacturer's certificate chain.</li>
				<li><code>enterprise</code> — direct, plus identifying info about the
					specific authenticator (only available in enterprise deployments).</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				this demo uses <code>none</code>. the demo isn't an enterprise rp; it
				doesn't need to attest to which authenticator vendor signed the
				credential. for a high-assurance flow (a corporate enrollment portal,
				say) <code>direct</code> + a vetted aaguid allowlist is the usual call.
			</p>

			<h3 class="passkey__h3">user verification vs user presence (UV / UP)</h3>
			<p>
				every assertion sets two bits in the authenticator data:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>UP</strong> (user presence) — a human poked the authenticator
					(touched the key, tapped the screen). almost always required.</li>
				<li><strong>UV</strong> (user verification) — the human proved who they
					are (biometric, pin). this demo requests
					<code>userVerification: "preferred"</code>; the authenticator fires
					UV if it can, otherwise just UP.</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				a "passwordless" flow demands UV; a "second factor" flow only needs
				UP because a password already covered identity. the rp inspects the
				bits server-side to confirm the policy actually fired.
			</p>

			<h3 class="passkey__h3">discoverable credentials (resident keys)</h3>
			<p>
				a discoverable credential is stored on the authenticator itself, keyed
				by rpID, so the browser can offer it at the lock screen with no
				username typed. the trade-off:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>discoverable</strong> — better UX, slot-limited on hardware
					keys (a yubikey holds ~25), and the rp does not need to know who
					the user is before issuing the challenge.</li>
				<li><strong>server-side allowList</strong> — the rp sends
					<code>allowCredentials</code> with the user's known credential ids;
					the authenticator picks one. unlimited count, but requires a
					username first.</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				this demo requests <code>residentKey: "preferred"</code> on register,
				then on authenticate sends an explicit <code>allowCredentials</code>
				list — that's the belt-and-suspenders posture most rps actually
				ship. platform authenticators (touch id, windows hello, face id)
				virtually always store the credential as discoverable regardless.
			</p>
		</section>
	</div>

	<script>
		import '../../scripts/passkey-demo';
	</script>
</BaseLayout>

<style is:global>
	body:has(.passkey) {
		background: #0a0320;
		color: #ffd6ec;
	}
</style>

<style>
	.passkey {
		max-width: 760px;
		width: 100%;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 32px 24px 80px;
		font-family: 'VT323', 'Courier New', monospace;
	}

	.passkey__head {
		margin-bottom: 24px;
	}

	.passkey__eyebrow {
		margin: 0 0 4px;
		font-family: 'Press Start 2P', 'VT323', monospace;
		font-size: 11px;
		letter-spacing: 0.3em;
		color: #00e5ff;
	}

	.passkey__title {
		margin: 0 0 12px;
		font-size: clamp(28px, 5vw, 40px);
		color: #ff7ec0;
		letter-spacing: 0.04em;
		text-shadow: 2px 2px 0 #321a44;
	}

	.passkey__lede {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: 18px;
		color: #ffd6ec;
	}

	.passkey__lede code,
	.passkey__copy code,
	.passkey__writeup code,
	.passkey__notice code {
		font-family: 'VT323', 'Courier New', monospace;
		background: rgba(255, 79, 168, 0.12);
		color: #ffb8e0;
		padding: 0 4px;
		border-radius: 3px;
	}

	.passkey__notice {
		margin: 0 0 32px;
		padding: 12px 16px;
		background: rgba(255, 215, 0, 0.06);
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 215, 0, 0.4);
		border-radius: 4px;
		color: #ffefb8;
		font-size: 16px;
		line-height: 1.5;
	}

	.passkey__notice strong {
		color: #ffd700;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.1em;
		font-family: 'Press Start 2P', 'VT323', monospace;
		font-size: 12px;
		margin-right: 6px;
	}

	.passkey__demo {
		display: grid;
		gap: 24px;
		padding: 20px;
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
		border: 1px solid rgba(0, 229, 255, 0.25);
		border-radius: 6px;
		margin-bottom: 40px;
	}

	.passkey__stored {
		padding: 10px 12px;
		background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4);
		border-left: 3px solid #00e5ff;
		font-size: 16px;
		color: #b8e6ff;
	}

	.passkey__stored[data-state="empty"] {
		border-left-color: #6e5a8a;
		color: #b8a0d8;
	}

	.passkey__row {
		display: grid;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	.passkey__h2 {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: 20px;
		color: #ff7ec0;
		letter-spacing: 0.06em;
		text-transform: lowercase;
	}

	.passkey__h3 {
		margin: 20px 0 6px;
		font-size: 17px;
		color: #00e5ff;
		letter-spacing: 0.04em;
		text-transform: lowercase;
	}

	.passkey__copy {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: 16px;
		line-height: 1.45;
	}

	.passkey__field {
		display: grid;
		gap: 4px;
		font-size: 15px;
	}

	.passkey__field span {
		color: #b8a0d8;
		text-transform: lowercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.08em;
		font-size: 13px;
	}

	.passkey__field input {
		padding: 8px 10px;
		background: #1a0e23;
		border: 1px solid #6e5a8a;
		border-radius: 3px;
		color: #ffd6ec;
		font-family: inherit;
		font-size: 16px;
	}

	.passkey__field input:focus-visible {
		outline: 2px solid #00e5ff;
		outline-offset: 1px;
	}

	.passkey__actions {
		display: flex;
		gap: 10px;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
	}

	.passkey__btn {
		padding: 8px 16px;
		background: #ff7ec0;
		color: #1a0e23;
		border: 2px solid #321a44;
		border-radius: 4px;
		box-shadow: 2px 2px 0 0 #321a44;
		font-family: 'Press Start 2P', 'VT323', monospace;
		font-size: 12px;
		cursor: pointer;
		transition: transform 80ms ease, background 80ms ease;
		text-transform: lowercase;
	}

	.passkey__btn:hover:not(:disabled),
	.passkey__btn:focus-visible:not(:disabled) {
		background: #ff4fa8;
		color: #fff9f3;
	}

	.passkey__btn:active:not(:disabled) {
		transform: translate(1px, 1px);
	}

	.passkey__btn:disabled {
		opacity: 0.5;
		cursor: not-allowed;
	}

	.passkey__btn--ghost {
		background: transparent;
		color: #b8a0d8;
		border-color: #6e5a8a;
		box-shadow: 2px 2px 0 0 #6e5a8a;
	}

	.passkey__btn--ghost:hover:not(:disabled),
	.passkey__btn--ghost:focus-visible:not(:disabled) {
		background: rgba(184, 160, 216, 0.1);
		color: #ffd6ec;
	}

	.passkey__status {
		margin: 0;
		min-height: 1.4em;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-family: 'VT323', 'Courier New', monospace;
	}

	.passkey__status[data-state="ok"] { color: #5fffaf; }
	.passkey__status[data-state="err"] { color: #ff6b8a; }
	.passkey__status[data-state="busy"] { color: #ffd700; }
	.passkey__status[data-state="idle"] { color: transparent; }

	.passkey__writeup p,
	.passkey__writeup ul {
		font-size: 16px;
		line-height: 1.5;
	}

	.passkey__writeup ul {
		padding-left: 20px;
		margin: 6px 0 10px;
	}

	.passkey__writeup li {
		margin-bottom: 4px;
	}

	.passkey__writeup strong {
		color: #ffd6ec;
	}
</style>
